This paper is about a new intermediate representation (IR) and compiler framework for deep learning models. It discusses the challenges of accommodating the rapidly diversifying landscape of DL models and hardware platforms, and presents Relay as a solution. Given the focus on DL models and their optimization, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.AR (Augmented Reality).
